ETHEKWINI Mayor Mxolisi Kaunda has condemned the killing of top rapper Kiernan Forbes, affectionately known as AKA. The Fela in Versace hitmaker was shot and killed outside a popular Durban restaurant on Florida Road on Friday, 10 February. Kaunda has called on the police to speed up the investigation and bring those responsible to book. “The news of AKA’s passing comes as a shock to us as we were looking forward to seeing him perform at the Durban All-white Concert at the Durban ICC next Saturday. We call upon community members who might have witnessed the incident to share information with the police,” Kaunda said in a statement. REGISTER TO COMMENT! He added that the killing, that took place on a popular nightlife street, would have an impact on the image of Durban’s hottest nightspots, that the municipality had worked hard to build over the years. ALSO READ: AKA's parents speak after his death! “The freedom of our residents is threatened each time a person is killed or robbed. We implore the police to be firm and act decisively in rooting out rouge elements that are behind the killing of innocent people. We remain committed to intensifying the fight against crime,” Kaunda said. Following news of AKA’s death, tributes have since been pouring in on social media. Media Statement 11 February 2023The Department of Sport, Arts and Culture mourns the passing of Artist and Rapper, Kiernen Forbes (AKA)Rest in peace SUPA MEGA.#RIPAKAPic @akaworldwide pic.twitter.com/j9viR5C5Rc  Crime in South Africa is out of control, and the assassination of civilians has become a norm.AKA was an indisputable talent and the music industry has lost a innovative artist. May His Soul Rest In Peace pic.twitter.com/fRCnDeTuxs 